      • valueOf

        public java.lang.Object valueOf(java.lang.String valueAsString)
                         throws java.lang.NumberFormatException,
                                java.text.ParseException
        Given the data value as a string, try to convert it to the appropriate Java wrapper object and return it. Any conversion errors will simply be re-thrown. Special cases:
        • BOOLEAN is true for
        • NUMBER is converted to BigDecimal
        • DATE values use the DATE_FORMAT pattern; if nulldate, return null
        • STRING values are returned as-is
        • OBJECT values are returned as-is
        Parameters:
        valueAsString -
        Returns:
        Integer value, Boolean value, etc.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NumberFormatException - if numeric conversion fails
        java.text.ParseException - if date conversion fails
